IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: PROVIDES MENTORS, COLLEGE SCHOLARSHIPS AND HOPE TO LOW-INCOME AT-RISK STUDENTS IN FLORIDA.
IRS990.MissionDesc: PROVIDES COLLEGE SCHOLARSHIPS AND MENTORING PROGRAMS FOR DESERVING LOW-INCOME CHILDREN WHOSE HOUSEHOLD INCOME FALLS BELOW 185% OF THE FEDERAL POVERTY GUIDELINES FROM MIDDLE SCHOOL THROUGH COLLEGE.
IRS990.Desc: TAKE STOCK IN CHILDREN USES A SUSTAINABLE PUBLIC-PRIVATE MODEL THAT ENABLES 97% OF OUR STUDENTS TO GRADUATE FROM HIGH SCHOOL AND 90% ENROLL INTO POSTSECONDARY EDUCATION WITH A FULL TUITION SCHOLARSHIP AND 72% GRADUATE WITH A POSTSECONDARY DEGREE. THIS PROGRAM HAS SERVED MORE THAN 39,000 OF FLORIDA'S CHILDREN AND PROVIDED MORE THAN $270 MILLION IN COLLEGE SCHOLARSHIPS TO DESERVING LOW-INCOME CHILDREN WHOSE HOUSEHOLD INCOME FALLS BELOW 185% OF THE FEDERAL POVERTY GUIDELINES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: TAKE STOCK IN CHILDREN AWARDS GRANTS TO AFFILIATED ORGANIZATIONS WITHIN THE 67 COUNTIES OF FLORIDA, USA. EACH RECIPIENT IS REQUIRED TO SIGN A MEMORANDUM OF UNDERSTANDING REGARDING THE APPROPIATE USE OF THE FUNDS. RECIPIENTS ARE ALSO REQUIRED TO SUBMIT QUARTERLY REPORTS ON THE USE OF THE FUNDS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED, REVIEWED AND PRESENTED TO THE FINANCE COMMITTEE FOR APPROVAL BEFORE BEING PRESENTED TO THE BOARD FOR FINAL APPROVAL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: WE MONITOR POTENTIAL CONFLICTS OF INTEREST WHEN WE SOLICIT SERVICES FROM A SUPPLIER AND IF A CONFLICT EXISTS WITH THE POTENTIAL SUPPLIER, IT WOULD THEN BE FULLY DISCLOSED TO THE BOARD FOR THEIR EVALUATION AS PER THE WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. ANY OTHER CONFLICTS OF INTEREST ARE ALSO ADDRESSED ON AN ONGOING BASIS AT DIRECTOR'S MEETINGS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE BOARD ESTABLISHES AND APPROVES OFFICER COMPENSATION. EMPLOYEES' COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY A COMPARISON OF COMPENSATION STRUCTURE FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS AND IS REVIEWED AND APPROVED BY THE PRESIDENT AND CEO.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
